Welcome, this is my new minecraft jailbreak map, where I have tried to introduce a unique idea to give the gamemode some more objective. Dont be afraid by the spawn, you start in the 'shop' but will soon be teleported to the cell area.

Changelog

- Fixed DeathRope continuity issue

- Fixed warmode death teleport

- Removed Creeper friendly-fire
- Added crash exploitation protection
- Added Climb Area





	**Map Features**

- Item Shop, with Diamond Currency
- Crafting Abilities (Create TNT, Pickaxes and more)
- Harvest-able wheat and pork to make Medic function
- Mining!
- Cavern Bunnyhopping
- DeathRope
- Nether
- DiamondTheft
- War Mode
- Tower Defence Mode
- And much more soon!


**Diamond Currency Explained**


**How CT gain Diamonds**

Both teams start with no diamonds
Diamonds have to be obtained by ordering a **terrorist** to mine diamonds hidden around the map
Diamonds mined will be added to the CT sides DiamondCount on the next round
Diamonds allow you to get better special items

**How T gain Diamonds**

Diamonds mined go to the Nether Vault
Terrorists have to get to the vault and steal the diamonds
Only 1 diamond can fit in each cart or they will fall out

JB_RAZOR_ELECTRIC (Also known as ba_jail_electric_razor_v7)
-----------------------
This map was intentionally designed to encourage terrorists to riot.  So it may seem T-biased for the first several weeks until people learn the map.  This map is hosted on possibly the best jailbreak server that there is: 204.8.219.194:27015.  I strongly recommend you look at how we set it up.

Feedback is also welcome on this, as I'm trying to get everything tied up for the final release.

==RELEASE NOTES==

Oct 28, 2009
============
Beta 4 Release
- Increased lighting in cell block by 4x
- Added some props and pictures to infirmary
- Modified several teleport destinations
- Modified solitary doors to always stay open once opened
- Fixed T-Buyzone in solitary cell (should work every round now)

A few of the less-known Secrets
===============================
One of the posts in infirmary will turn the entrance of the infirmary into a teleport to the basement.  There is a two second timer on this teleport.

The second step from the top on the left-most diving board will open up a teleport above the first bench on the left.  You must use the diving board to access it.

All of the secrets in version 6 can be found in this version.  The pistols are in the same locations, including the hidden pistol behind the big cage.

There is a door to the top of cells from soccer.  The only way to get there is to side strafe off of the soccer wall where the opening into the soccer field is.  There is an invisible platform and a door.

There is a way into the awp spot from kitchen.  On the upper left corner of the metal door to kitchen (on the inside), there is a button that will open up the grate, as well as create an invisible ledge that will help you up.

In armory, you can throw a nade into the gun room, to activate the 7 hidden teleports.  These teleports can be used by CT's to access several different parts of the map.  Keep in mind that there is a two second timer on the button, so you have to move quick, or work with other CT's to utilize this feature.  CT's who learn to use this feature, will gain a HUGE advantage over the terrorists.

It is a jailbreak map. A large octagon, with 5 octagon shaped buildings and an off ground walkway around the perimeter. The center building is a place for people to camp and such, its a two story building with 3 ways to the second floor. Two opposite buildings are cells, with 16 wall mounted cell pod things in each. The other two buildings are medic and gunroom. Gunroom is fenced off, but has multiple ways to get past the fence. The entrance to gunroom is raised off the ground with some boxes to get up. 16 ct spawn points in gunroom.

This map took a long time to make, and is still in its primary stages.  Hopefully over the next several months it'll get better.  There are secrets, but they are NOT easy to get too without practice.

The CT's start in a Buyzone.  Which means the server admins hosting this map need to ensure that the CT's have cash to begin with.
